  "notes": [
    "Org switch mechanism: session cookie is httpOnly and scoped server-side. Calling ExchangeSession with a new organizationId rewrites the session; the old org context is lost in the same browser tab.",
    "No X-Org-ID header or client-redacted org cookie is used. Each request relies on the server-side session to know which org is active.",
    "After ExchangeSession, the webapp re-issues GetMember, GetOrganization, ListOrganizations with the new context. CLI should do the same when implementing `ana org switch`.",
    "Requires existing authenticated session (cookie). Returns 401 if unauthenticated.",
    "memberId differs per org: same user has one memberId per (user, org) pair. `id` is an integer member row id; `memberId` is the UUID used in RBAC calls."
